manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Provide a fan and heatsink cooling solution to any standard Socket 775/T desktop CPU This Socket T/775 cooler is designed specifically for the Intel Socket 775 (Socket T) range of processors, including Intel Core 2 Duo and Intel Core 2 Quad, Core 2 Duo Extreme CPUs. The CPU cooler features a large aluminum heatsink that maximizes dissipation of the heat around the CPU, as well a low-noise 95mm fan that provides up to 50 CFM of air circulation, helping to keep the CPU cooler for optimized performance. The Socket 775/T cooler/fan offers simple installation, providing tool-less clips for easy connection to the motherboard.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for DIY power supply or load projects
reviews.reviewText: I got 2 of these heat sinks to cool the load transistors in a DIY DC load kit that I built. The transistors can pass about 25 amps each (x4), so these heat sinks need to handle a fair amount of heat (~100W). The fans generate a lot of cooling and the heat sinks get pretty warm, but they work really well. And for $12 they are pretty reasonable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 50x50x41mm Socket 7/370 CPU Cooler Fan w/ Heatsink
reviews.reviewText: This fan with heat sink were well on my Pentium 166 & 233 CPU boards.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Revised review -- product was OK after all but does need instructions
reviews.reviewText: Originally sent a negative review last week because I could not get the pins to go into the holes of my 775 board. It turns out the fan's pins were shipped in the "installed" configuration rather than "ready to install", and I was not familiar with these pin types. After some work I was able to get the pins set up right. An instruction manual would have been helpful for us novices so I could spot the problem. Otherwise all seems good and it did ship with a small packet of thermal paste.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good on Steam Deck
reviews.reviewText: This can be powered by a USB-C adapter through the Steam Deck itself. Good match with JSAUX back plate.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 14, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Coolls what's hot!
reviews.reviewText: Bought this to replace the OEM Intel cooler on my ancient Core2Duo. The original plastic clips failed and stopped cooling the CPU. I got this as a replacement. Works great. Some people complained about the noise, but really, it's a cooling fan for a mid-2000's PC. It's not that loud.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 29, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good quality heatsink and fan
reviews.reviewText: Very good fan, a little loud but quiet enough with the case on. The heatsinks itself is good and substantial enough to cover the socket, without interfering with components, end the clip is easy to operate with just the right amount of tension. Used on a Pentium 200 non-MMX in a Compaq Prolinea. Included adapter to Molex 4 pin. If the fan speed bothered me enough I could run it at 5v and it would probably still be adequate.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars outstanding CPU fan & heatsink
reviews.reviewText: I have always found StarTech products to be good quality, and this item is no exception. The fan and heat sink are slightly larger than the Intel assembly that came with the processor.Executive summary: you don't have to remove your motherboard to install the retainer plate.A note about installation: when I saw pictures of this product I was unsure about how to install the plate that contains the screw holes. The included retainer plate mounts under the motherboard's base plate, and the screws are long enough to protrude through the motherboard and its base plate to make contact with the retainer panel.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 8, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Bad experience with this product
reviews.reviewText: I have tried for days to mount this product into the mobo.. despite both comply with the standard and the holes and claps match, there is no way to do it, it is simply awful, the plastic claps will never align to enter properly on the mobo holes, I have manage to insert 3 of them, but never made it with the 4th. The mechanism to do this is terrible, the design from this point of view is terrible. The fan has a 3-pin connector… why? why you do this with a 3-pin connector? Most mobos have 4 pin sockets to handle the CPU fan. I had to buy a separate adapter 3pin to 4-pin to be able to connect it. The support department never answers. As I bought this from overseas It will cost me the same it costs to return it. I finally had to order a new CPU cooler (Screws one). Terrible experience for me with this one, and a waste of time and money. Awful product.Honestly... I feel robbed

reviews.reviewTitle: Quando il prodotto funziona va bene.
reviews.reviewText: Chi lo ha progettato ne capisce qualcosa sul raffreddamento delle vecchie CPU Pentium 4. Complimenti.
Parfaitement adapté, extrêmement silencieux, fait son job ! Merci !
Excelente calidad!!Estoy instalando y desde la prueba funciona perfectamente

Gute preisgünstige Kühllösung, die ich auf einen 100MHz 68060 mit Thermal Glue geklebt habe. Bei 12V ist de Lüfter allerdings recht laut und für mich unnötig schnell. Bei 5V läuft er nicht verlässlich an, sodass ich einen Regler dazwischen verwende und so voll zufrieden bin.

reviews.reviewTitle: Llegó súper rápido, al día siguiente!
reviews.reviewText: Llegó súper rápido, al día siguiente!Ojo! Es de una conexión de 3 pines, no de 4 y no lo específica en la descripción del producto. El fan cooler es de baja calidad, la base trae tornillos plásticos de presión muy débiles, las puntas de este plástico quebradizo se parten fácilmente al intentar ajustar a los orificios de la placa base. Tiene buena potencia y no es demasiado ruidoso, aunque su base disipadora es completamente de aluminio, en comparación con el original de Intel que trae un núcleo de cobre. Mi ventilador Intel ya viejo estaba fallando y la ventaja es que se puede adaptar este ventilador a la base original de Intel porque es la medida exacta. Queda ver en el transcurso del tiempo y uso que tal trabaja y si aguanta.
